            "attributionText": "from The Century Dictionary.",
            "sourceDictionary": "century",
            "text": "A religious denomination found in Essex, Sussex, Surrey, and principally in Kent, England, which believes that one may immediately cease from sin and become perfect in moral life and in spiritual perception. They therefore have no preachers, creeds, ordinances, or church organization. They also profess to rely wholly upon prayer for the cure of disease. Also called <internalXref urlencoded=\"Plumstead%20Peculiars\">Plumstead Peculiars</internalXref>, from the place in which the sect originated. <strong>Synonyms</strong> <em>Particular</em>, etc. See <internalXref urlencoded=\"special\">special</internalXref>.",
